Package com.github.kaktushose.jda.commands.dispatching

Class CommandContext

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.github.kaktushose.jda.commands.dispatching.CommandContext
  • public class CommandContext
extends Object
    This class models a command execution. The Parser constructs a new CommandContext for each valid event received. The CommandContext is then passed through the execution chain until it is then transformed into a CommandEvent.
    Since:
    2.0.0
    Version:
    2.0.0
    Author:
    Kaktushose

      • getPossibleCommands

        public List<CommandDefinition> getPossibleCommands()
        Gets a list of CommandDefinitions that match the input. This list gets populated if and only if the command routing fails because more than one matching command was found. If no matching command was found or if the command routing succeeded, this list will be empty.
        Returns:
        a possibly-empty list of CommandDefinitions that match the input
